        <div class="tabs-panel is-active" id="panel1">
            <div style="padding-left: 5px;padding-right: 5px;padding-top: 5px;padding-bottom: 5px;background-color: #f7f7f7;">
                <h3>Version: 3.8.1</h3>
                <p MadCap:conditions="Primary.do-not-publish">Available in preview deployment:&#160;August 31, 2022</p>
                <p>Deployment date:&#160;September 6, 2022</p>
                <h4>Features and enhancements</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>The Device health page is now available by default. You can disable this feature by setting the <span class="code">FeatureFlags</span> registry key to <span class="code">DeviceHealthOff</span>.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Bug fixes</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>Okta Verify erroneously recreated the desktop icon when the app was updated. <span class="code">(OKTA-498870)</span></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Users encountered Okta Verify activation issues <span class="code">(OKTA-480514)</span>:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p>During account enrollment, the dialog box for enabling Windows Hello wasn’t in the foreground for users to provide input.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Authentication with Windows Hello didn’t succeed on the first attempt.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>During authentication, the app didn’t return to the previous state in some scenarios.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
